 applications using WML/WAP to make web applications compliant with mobile\ndevices.',NULL),(142,NULL,'Reusability: The support for POJOâ€™s allows developers to use Java classes developed for one part of the web\napplication to be easily used in another part. A second advantage is allowing the use of Java classes developed in\nprevious projects, e.g. construct a UI from a set of reusable UI components.\n',NULL),(145,NULL,'\nLearnability: This depends mainly on the type of developer a developer familiar with component-base coding will\nbe able to learn working with JSF a lot faster than a developer used to action-based coding.',NULL),(143,NULL,'Extendibility: JSF offers a basic set of standard, reusable UI components that enable page authors and application\ndevelopers to quickly and easily construct UIs for web applications.\nJSF allows a component writer to extend the standard components to enhance their functionality or create custom\ncomponents. Since the custom components can be build on top of existing components (through inheritance) they\ncan easily use the functionality of the existing components.\n',NULL),(152,'verypositive','dasdasdadasdasda adsdas',3);
